Other  sections of the game may have its own rules (such as the Chat Room, Game Forum.)  These rules are an addition to the Terms of Service, not a replacement.  Violation of these rules is considered to be a violation of the Terms of  Service and will be dealt with accordingly.
20.  PLAYER STAFF INTERACTION
Both  players and staff are expected to coexist in a polite and respectful  environment. This applies to professional interaction only, as there are  instances when the staff member is acting in the capacity of a player, and not  an administrator. This is not to say a staff member may become abusive and  claim they were acting in a player capacity, but it does mean a staff member  need not be stoic at all times. They're volunteers, and need to relax/get into  arguments too. This should never be the case in professional settings (i.e. Helpdesk  requests).
21.  COMMUNITY GUIDELINES
Since  people of diverse ages, backgrounds, religions, and nationalities play the  Service, it is expected that the players will refrain from speech that is  deliberately inflammatory, excessively vulgar, and/or personally derogatory. In  other words: No flaming and keep the "trash talk" to a minimum. This  applies to the general chat (public and private) as well as the messages  (public and private). Pushing excessive quantities of chat (public or private)  into the game, whether directed at the entire game or at a particular player is  considered spamming.
The  public chat and forums are strictly english, as the majority of the game population speak English as their primary language, and it is impossible to provide adequate moderation in every language.
In  addition, using the Service to promote the distribution of or access to warez,  MP3s, or other illegal software or products is strictly forbidden and will not  be tolerated.
Using  the Service to distribute pornography or access to pornography of any kind is  strictly forbidden and will not be tolerated.
